Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph list

list

Purpose:
  Enumerate Wiki Graph objects from a located Wiki Graph URI.

Use when:
  - You need objects of a kind without a text query, such as all chapters or all entities.

Usage:
  wikigraph <scope-uri> [--query <query>] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]

Returns:
  - URI-addressable objects in document order.

Notes:
  - Scope URIs enumerate without query text.
  - Use `<located-wikg-uri>/chapter`, `<located-wikg-uri>/entity`, `<located-wikg-uri>/triple`, or `<located-wikg-uri>/chunk` to choose the collection.
  - Some chapters are structural table-of-contents nodes that organize child chapters; missing generated artifacts alone does not make them abnormal.
  - Lens position controls scope: `<archive-uri>/entity` lists archive-wide entities, while `<chapter-uri>/entity` lists entities scoped to one chapter.
  - Use `<archive-uri>/entity` for an archive-wide entity inventory. Use `<chapter-uri>/entity` only when you need one chapter.
  - Use `_` as an any-value placeholder in triple pattern lenses such as `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1/_/Q2`.
  - Trailing triple placeholders may be omitted: `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1` means `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1/_/_`.
  - Put the lens after a chapter URI, such as `<chapter-uri>/entity`, to list within one chapter.
  - Add `--query <query>` when you have query text.
  - Add `--evidence` or `--evidence <n>` to include source evidence previews on entity and triple results.
  - Evidence previews include 2 nearby sentences before and after by default. Use `--context 0` for exact cited ranges.
  - Add `--backlinks` to include reverse references on top-level source results; nested evidence sources are not expanded.
  - Read `wikigraph help retrieval` before choosing `--limit`, `--all`, `--json`, or `--jsonl`.
  - Use `wikigraph next <cursor>` for any returned `nextCursor`.
  - Use `wikigraph help uri` before constructing Wiki Graph URIs; bare filesystem paths are not valid object command inputs.

Examples:
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/chapter
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/entity
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/chapter/3/entity
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/triple/_/_/Q178561
